OL,3,CEx Kent police officer admits fraud
OL,4,Cusing horse racing syndicate
OL,6,F"Unknown to members, in fact, the
OL,7,Fdefendant was operating a massive
OL,8,Ffraud," the prosecutor added.
OL,10,FThe court heard about #44 million was
OL,11,Fpaid into the scheme, an estimated #34
OL,12,Fmillion of which was paid back out to
OL,13,Fmembers, with a shortfall of around
OL,14,F#10 million.
OL,16,FThe scheme started out with family and
OL,17,Ffriends as clients but grew to more
OL,18,Fthan 6,000 members, and had a waiting
OL,19,Flist of 3,000 people at the time it
OL,20,Fcollapsed.
